              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/germ-358" class="program-course-title">
              GERM 358 Franz Kafka (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-26844" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Languages, Literatures and Cultures (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      German (Arts)              : This course will look at the works on Franz Kafka, a "classic" modernist author, in three characteristic genres: the story, the novel, and the short prose piece. A selection of Kafka's letters and diary entries as well as critical approaches to his work will also be studied.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Paul Peters (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Fall</li>
              <li>Given in English</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

