                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/germ-365" class="program-course-title">
              GERM 365 Language of Media from Manuscript to Hypertext (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-26858" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Languages, Literatures and Cultures (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      German (Arts)              : The history of communications media and their impact on our language and thought discussions of literary works in a variety of media (book, radio, film, television, hypertext) by authors such as Goethe, Kafka, Borges, Brecht, Beckett, Sontag and DeLillo.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              This course is not scheduled for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

